== General

Hi!

Banditvis is an open source project to visualise the origin of networked attacks.
In detail it uses fail2ban to detect, GeoIP to locate and Mapnik to visualise.

== Requirements

* fail2ban

* Python >= 2.5.2 (Debian: python, http://www.python.org/ )
* Python GeoIP >= 1.2.1 (Debian: python-geoip, http://www.maxmind.com/app/python/)
* Python Mapnik >= 0.5.1 (Debian: python-mapnik, http://mapnik.org/)

* PostgreSQL >= 8.3.12 (Debian: postgresql, http://www.postgresql.org/)
* PostGIS >= 1.3.3 (Debian: postgresql-8.3-postgis, http://postgis.refractions.net/ )

